name: The Earth Army's Last Secret Weapon!!
The Fated Showdown: Son Goku vs Vegeta

description:
The fur flies in FULL COLOR for Antarctic's latest release by fan favorite Richard Moore!
Chimeras: genetically-engineered creatures, part human, part animal; faster, stronger and deadlier than both. Kat and Caleb are "chims" scraping out a living in the prison-city known as The Pound, where survival of the fittest is the only law. Created for combat in off-world environments, they are now thievesthe best in the city. There's no score they won't take down. But being the best means making enemies, and Kat and Caleb have more than their share. When one of the biggest, Darius Blackeye, hires them to hijack a shipment of high-tech arms, the pair has to wonder what he wants morethe weapons, or to eliminate the competition?

You know how solicitations sometimes read, "This is the issue that changes everything!" Well, #5 is the issue that changes everything. After coming face-to-face with a Triplet he thought he already killedanda shootout with a gun-slinging hairstylist, the only question is will Cowboy Ninja Viking be left alive to enjoy it? Need more? Fine... Snikt!

DYNAMITE ENTERTAINMENT presents an all-new, Battlestar Galactica event featuring the DYNAMITE Debut of Javier Grillo-Marxuach (ya know, the guy behind such hit shows as Lost and Medium) as he unleashes the Cylon Apocalypse! After the events of last issue, in which the classic crew of the Battlestar Galactica discovered a new path to Earth, Adama decides on a course of action to take the battle to the Cylons and unleash his own Apocalypse on humanity's greatest enemies. Plus: Cylons invade the Galactica!

In this issue: All-Out War as the Galactica and her Viper's do battle with the Cylons and their Raiders as Adama has ordered the virus released against the Cylon Empire! Buit, all doesn't go as planned for Starbuck as he finds himself left behind on the Cylon world!

The Cylon Apocalypse comes to a Kobol-shattering conclusion! In this issue Starbuck races to flee the doomed Cylon homeworld as Adama and the Galactica wage a battle like none we've ever seen, against a deadly new Cylon threat! Will the fleet be able to prevent the Cylons from following them on their course to Earth! Find out as this special mini-series event concludes!

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
In "Terrible Swift Sword," it's a beautiful fall knight -- and The MAZE Agency's Jennifer and Gabe are camping with their friends, the Rydell family. Aside from Gabe being a tenderfoot, there's tension in the nighttime air: Carly, the Rydell's 15-year-old daughter, has become involved with "The Church of Michael," a religious cult! What's more, Judah and Sister Ruth have arrived from the cult -- bringing with them mayhem and murder!

*This issue again has no editor credit, however it can be assumed that this issue was edited by regular series editor, David Campiti.
name: Terrible Swift Sword

description: An elaborate medieval fantasy plot benefits from the impressive 3-D effects of Ray Zone in this involved one-shot. Sketch was once a warrior, but now serves as a royal artist. But his life is far from a collection of still-lifes. With the help of the white mage Gahan, Sketch infuses his art with magic to fight against the evil magician Shard, who seeks to rule the land with a powerful gem. Only Sketch, wielding his paints and canvas, can drain Shards power through an enchanted portrait and halt this diabolical threat, restoring peace to the kingdom.
name: Against Blackshard: 3-D - The Saga of Sketch, the Royal Artist

volume.name: Against Blackshard: 3-D - The Saga of Sketch, the Royal Artist

description:
The Panzer Mark IV lay silent and motionless in a museum in Germany, the dummy crew staring lifelessly ahead. It was one of over eight thousand produced throughout the Second World War, just another ordinary tank.

But then came the night in the 1970's when lightning crashed and thunder boomed - and the strangest vengeance mission ever was sparked into life as that twenty-five tone Panzer Mark IV began to move...
name: Back From the Dead

description:
After being saved from an Arctic storm by a US submarine. the last thing you'd expect a pair of fugitives to do would be to paddle right back to the Japanese infested island they'd just escaped from.

But that's exactly what Hugo Hoad and his Eskimo friend intended doing, for Hugo had a score to settle with the Japs. He'd watched them gun down his father in cold blood and now he was out for revenge!
name: A Score To Settle

description:
Nobby Clark and Lanky Lymburn were a tough pair of regular soldiers. Simon Smythe was new to war, but he was lucky to have these two rogues help him brave his baptism of fire. It also helped that they all served in a regiment steeped in the bravery and tradition which put backbone into men.

That glory only lasted, though, until the fateful battle when the regiment lost its honour. The shocked survivors of that sad day now faced a tougher task than any of the unit's previous heroes - the struggle to march again with pride in the regiment...
name: For the Regiment!

description: "Dive! Dive! Dive!" screamed the U-boat's captain. But even as they slipped away into the murky depths there was no respite for the battle-weary submariners. Their predator closed in, dropping depth-charges, each thunderous explosion closer than the last...
name: Run the Gauntlet

description:
At the height of the second Anglo-Afghan war in the late 1800s, Captain James Wilkinson of the British Royal Engineers - the Sappers - was given the job of building a strategically important bridge.

Working in a war zone was difficult enough; he didn't need the problems caused by a pair of fellow officers and Russian interference raising tensions in the area. That, though, is what he got.

James knew there was a fight brewing some time. And that time was now!
name: The Fighting Sapper

description:
The Aegean Sea, lying between Greece and Turkey is a huge expanse of bright blue water peppered with tiny islands. In 1943, the area was so far away from any British air base that Axis pilots there had nothing to worry about.

Until, that was, a British planner decided to stick a pair of floats on a Spitfire and set up a secret base slap bang in the middle of it. For pilot Johnny Cooper the fun was about to begin.
name: Aegean Ace

description:
Mesopotamia, 1914.

Young Harry Powell was new to the Royal Flying Corps and its fight against the Turks. Although a keen pilot, he lacked confidence in the air. His confidence fell even lower after the death of a fellow flyer.

Now under increasing pressure from a glory-hunting superior officer, Harry would need all his courage to survive...
name: Desert Dogfight

description:
Duels have been fought throughout history. They have been fought to the sounds of clashing sabres and crack of pistols.

One duel was different. It was fought to the earth-shattering roar of big guns, the mighty artillery pieces of World War One. And the two men fighting, Lieutenant Harry Bowden and Hauptmann Franz Boedeker, were not in the relative safety of the batteries... they were right where the shells were landing.
name: Roar Of The Guns

description:
Two young soldiers - one British, one German - were about to go into battle as the Second World War broke out.

Like many of their friends, their fathers had seen action years earlier in the First World War.

But for this particular pair of warriors, there was a bizarre link which, one day, would end in bitter tragedy...
name: Fathers and Sons

description:
When tough storm trooper Kurt Steyer returned to Germany in 1918, he decided he'd had enough of fighting. But as his Fatherland descended into anarchy, he found himself drawn into battle once more... and again he was fighting for his life.

This time, though, he couldn't be sure just who his enemies were...
name: Storm Trooper

description:
They called them "Mongrel Squadron"... the oddest bunch to take to the air in World War One - their aircraft a strange mixture of British and captured German types.

The pilots were proven troublemakers who had been given one last chance - their tactics a blend of cheek and cool courage.

Yet their leader, an ex-cavalryman, was determined to mould them into the most effective fighting unit on the Western Front!
name: Mongrel Squadron

description:
Transferred from the army to the air force in the early days of war in the air, Austrian Karl Littman began to wonder if his fighting days were over - all he seemed to do was fly boring patrols. His observer did all the shooting and that was from a very safe distance.

So Karl decided to liven things up and really make the sparks fly. Unfortunately he was a bit too successful and it began to look as though he was the one who'd get his wings clipped - permanently.
name: Valley of Death

description:
During the First World War, Captain Gus Brodie and Lieutenant Dave Runthorpe of the Royal Engineers were given the job of destroying strategically vital Romanian oil installations. Somehow, though, they found themselves in charge of tons of valuable Russian petrol and on the run from the German Army.

Their mission had gone wildly off-target, but they had help in the unlikely form of some escaped British prisoners and local villagers. But even all that help couldn't turn their ancient, slow-moving river barges into a fighting force... could it?
name: Barging Into Battle

description:
In the desperate early days of the First World War, the Kaiser's army swept the French and British aside, shattering their armies into pockets of badly-mauled men struggling to survive. One such group was a signaller, a dragoon who had lost his horse, and a bunch of Lancers.

Could they link up with the rest of their retreating army? And would the battlefield bike be a help or a hindrance?
name: Battlefield Bike

description:
As a nation, the Swiss have remained neutral in many wars, preferring not to get involved in other people's battles.

At times, though, they have got caught up in the fighting - such as when the armies of Napoleon Bonaparte overran their homeland.

That's when the French discovered that the Swiss really could fight. And that few could fight harder than the fighting brothers.
name: The Fighting Brothers

description:
When Japan declared war on China in 1941, a squad of British Royal Engineers building a bridge in Zheijiang Province were unexpectedly cut off from their unit. They resolved to return to their own lines but, with no combat experience, minimal rations and no radio or compass, things weren't looking too good.

Some unlikely help came in the form of a bookish French orphan who had escaped from a mission building before the Japs razed it to the ground.

Would the survive the jungle and all its terrors on their escape from Zheijiang?
name: Escape From Zheijiang

description:
The two jets hurtled towards each other, each travelling at over 500mph, all guns blazing.

Both pilots were German - from the same squadron, in fact. But one was determined to put an end to an evil, last-ditch Nazi plan called ""Operation Extinction"" - and the other was equally determined to stop him!
name: Operation Extinction

description:
The Japs were sweeping through the Far East, conquering everything that lay before them. The oil-rich Emirate of Saranei should have fallen next as a matter of course.

But Lieutenant Harry James, RN, ordered to get the young Emir to the safety of Australia, was determined not only to fight tooth and nail to ensure the success of his mission - but also to show the Japs that the underdog could bite back savagely!
name: Teeth of the Dragon

description:
Silently, except for the wind whipping over its wide wings, the Horsa glider swept in towards the ground - where death and destruction waited at the hands of the German forces prepared to defend their homeland.

The glider's pilot and co-pilot had faced up to similar dangers many times before in their tough war, but this would be their last fight together...
name: Glide into Danger

description:
No, Herr Hauptman, I have not been out in the sun too long. With my own eyes I saw itit had six sides, as many guns as a pocket-battleship and moved like a great crab at about one hundred kilometres an hour. A tank? No, it wasnt a tank. It was more like a monster
And after that report from a badly-frightened radio operator came into Nazi HQ, a wave of fear swept the desert. What was the Thing that struck from the shadows like a prehistoric beast? Only four men knewand they were all listed as dead!
name: Desert Monster

description:
Gremlins, leprechauns call them what you like they all had it in for Lieutenant Johnny Dawson. He was the sort of bloke whose Sten would suddenly jam for no reason, or hed be the one in a million whod be issued with the grenade with a faulty fuse.
Yes, Johnny had a real JINX. He didnt like it, the top brass didnt like it and, most important, Johnnys men didnt like it. In fact if his luck didnt change soon hed have a mutiny on his hands.
name: Johnny the Jinx

description:
To be in Captain Dick Barbary's special demolition team, THE BARBARIANS ", you had to be plenty tough. You had to be able to scale a cliff like a Commando, fight like a cornered tiger and, above all, handle explosives - all kinds of explosives - like a true professional.

No wonder they were called -

THE DEADLY MEN
name: The Deadly Men

description:
Sam Blake was fed up. He'd come from Canada to join the R.A.F. to fight Nazis as a fully qualified pilot, only to find he'd to learn to fly all over again, the official way.

Then they kicked him out of a fighter squadron. "Too reckless and irresponsible" they said. "Give him a bomber. He can't pull any wild stunts in that."

But Sam saw this as a chance for real glory. He flew his bomber as if it were a sprightly Spitfire and even turned on Nazi night fighters. What a guy!
name: Glory Hunter

description:
The man called Sketch was once one of the kings greatest warriors. Now, as the royal artist, he uses his fairest talent in the service of the king, painting portraits and portraying battles.

During one of those battles, Sketch dares to paint the portrait of the evil mage known as Blackshard. Blackshard captures not only Sketch, but the powerful gems attached to the foreheads of three sacred stallions as well.

Blackshard seems unstoppable, but Sketch must defeat this terrible enemy if he is to regain the one thing Blackshard has stolen which Sketch holds dearer than lifeSketchs own soul.

3D version of Maxx #1. (Plus new story by Sam Kieth and Jim Sinclair.)

Main story: Maxx busts into the series by emerging from his cardboard box home and saves an attractive woman from her would be attackers. But when the cops show up all they find is a large purple homeless man in a purple suite. Unfortunately with the Maxx in custody it leaves the attractive woman open for Mr. Gone.

While in police custody Maxx slips into the Outback and under attack by a throng of Is. With one quick swipe the Maxx frees himself and we get our first look at the Leopard Queen.

Maxxs social worker Julie receives two phone calls; the first is a disturbing voice that Julie takes for just some creep the second informs her of Maxxs incarceration. Now free the Maxx and Julie spot a suspicious looking figure using phones in an unusual way.

We also see Mr. Gone enter a laundry matt and leave him as he attacks another girl.
Written by Peter Quinones. Art work by Kelley Jones (Batman, Deadman, Sandman)and Jim Sinclair (The Maxx)
